Boot Configuration Lock;
000 - Unlocked (fuses can be read, sensed, burned or overridden in the corresponding 
OTP shadow register);
xx1 - WP (Write Protect, the controlled field can not be burned);
x1x - OP (Over-ride Protect, the controlled field shadow registers can not be over-written);
1xx - RP (Read Protect, the controlled field can be sensed only, but can't be read from 
shadow registers)

